4
00:00:10.300 --> 00:00:13.070
This case study illustrates
a number of things.

5
00:00:13.070 --> 00:00:16.820
First, it shows how we apply
the idea of thinking backwards.

6
00:00:16.820 --> 00:00:19.130
By way of review,
this means the following.

7
00:00:19.130 --> 00:00:21.480
We start with the decision
we want to make.

8
00:00:21.480 --> 00:00:25.360
We then determine what analysis
outputs would help make that decision.

9
00:00:25.360 --> 00:00:28.270
We design the analysis that
creates those outputs.

10
00:00:28.270 --> 00:00:31.670
We determine what data is needed for
analysis and how to get it.

11
00:00:31.670 --> 00:00:33.980
And finally, we execute the analysis.

12
00:00:33.980 --> 00:00:37.520
The example also illustrates how different
types of analytics can be used in

13
00:00:37.520 --> 00:00:39.800
one larger effort, and
how quantitative and

14
00:00:39.800 --> 00:00:43.500
qualitative considerations contribute
to business decision making.

15
00:00:43.500 --> 00:00:47.090
Finally, it illustrates a couple of
ways in which data can be displayed and

16
00:00:47.090 --> 00:00:49.420
presentation materials created.

17
00:00:49.420 --> 00:00:51.370
In this video we'll tee
up the situation and

18
00:00:51.370 --> 00:00:54.400
walk through the thought process
leading up to the analysis.

19
